 BY ABUBAKAR ALIDU UNIDENTIFIED gunmen have abducted the daughter of a former Speaker of the Jigawa State House of Assembly, Isah Zakari, and two other persons. The ex-Speakerâ€™s 25-year-old daughter, Zainab Isah Zakari, was whisked to an unknown destination, along with one Sule Isah, a septuagenarian. The gunmen, suspected to be kidnappers, were said to have stormed Bosuwa village in Maigatari Local Government Area of the state, where they perpetrated the dastardly act, after reportedly kidnapping a popular businessman in Jahun Local Government Area of Jigawa. Police Public Relations Officer in the state, SP Abdu Jinjiri, who confirmed the incident, disclosed that a police officer that was on duty was gunned down. He however said the Command had deployed officers to fish out the culprits and rescue the victims.  